This is a simple function for managing virtualenvs. It is similar to
virtualenvwrapper but with fewer features. Use it to activate, deactivate,
and switch virtualenvs. Currently there are two hooks provided: post-activate
and post-deactivate.

p.sh is meant to be sourced and not run directly

requires:
    PYENV to be set to your base dir for virtualenvs

provides:
    p

INSTALL:
    put into ~/.bashrc or the like:
        export PYENV=~/my_virtual_envs
        source /path/to/p.sh

USAGE:
    p --help
